  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">You can leverage your catalysts as components for a wider variety of spells. You can add Wands and Spellhearts to the items you can use for Spell Catalyst.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">When you use a Spellheart, you can use the Spellheart’s traits to check for qualifying traits. When used as a catalyst, the Spellheart becomes inert, unable to be used normally or for Spell Catalyst until your next daily preparations.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">When you use a wand, the wand’s charge must not have been spent yet, and you can use the wand’s spell to check for qualifying traits. When you use the wand as a catalyst, the wand loses its charge as if it had been used for the day.</span></p><p><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">In addition, when you use Spell Catalyst, you can negate up to 2 points of focus point costs.</span></p>"
